org.apache.juneau

Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.juneau.Session
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BeanSession

    public abstract class Session
extends Object
    A one-time-use non-thread-safe object that's meant to be used once and then thrown away.

    Serializers and parsers use session objects to retrieve config properties and to use it as a scratchpad during serialize and parse actions.

      • getLocale

        public Locale getLocale()
        Configuration property: Locale.

        The locale is determined in the following order:

        1. locale parameter passed in through constructor.
        2. Context.CONTEXT_locale entry in parameter passed in through constructor.
        3. Context.CONTEXT_locale setting on bean context.
        4. Locale returned by Locale.getDefault().
        Returns:
        The session locale.
        See Also:
        Context.CONTEXT_locale
